Questions:
Which aspect of the HOPE-Genomics study is considered experimental?
A) Completing standard surveys about cancer and genomics after receiving genomic test results;
B) Interacting with a web-based education tool designed to improve understanding of personal genomic test results;
C) Undergoing genomic testing to identify changes in DNA related to cancer risk;
D) Receiving standard medical care and treatment at City of Hope.

Correct answer: B) Interacting with a web-based education tool designed to improve understanding of personal genomic test results.

If you decide not to participate in the HOPE-Genomics study, what is the alternative option available to you?
A) You will be required to participate in a different study; 
B) You will not receive any further treatment at City of Hope; 
C) You will continue to receive standard care without participating in the study; 
D) You will be given access to a different web-based education tool.

Correct answer: C

If you experience any emotional upset during the study or have questions about your rights as a research subject, whom should you contact?

A) The Institutional Review Board (IRB) at City of Hope; 
B) The principal investigator, Dr. Stacy Gray; 
C) Your personal physician; 
D) The National Institutes of Health (NIH)

Correct answer: B) The principal investigator, Dr. Stacy Gray;
